-Quads for 900.<br>
-Slowable.<br>
-Unresistable AE 400 DD with single buff dispell, every 15ish seconds.<br>
-Single-Target Mana Drain (I think.)<br>
-100K to 200K HP.<br>
<br>
Minus the MT, all raiders should be decked out in HP gear. When buffing, get 3-4 dummy buffs up front. The very first buff is preferrably an insta-click. Click it every time the AE hits you.<br>
<br>
You can only fight him in the pit, period. Or near the HoT door, if you wish. How it is done is the puller brings Dozekar to a waiting Defensived Main Tank in one of the corners, perferrably the left one. All other raiders are in the cubby. For roughly 10 seconds, only the MT will engage, taunting and taking aggro. A fast CH or DL rotation is immediately placed on the MT.<br>
<br>
10 Seconds in, all other tanks enter at max melee range (the furthest you can stand from the mob, and still hit it... pets are great demonstrations of this). Shamans and Magicians immediately need to start trying to land Malosini on him (Malo/Mala first, of course), as well as tash/OOS. Then get him slowed. Upon landing slow, slow the rotation. All tanks continue to engage. Tanks who get a lot of aggro (Rogues/Pallies) may need to back out occasionally if they are overaggroing. It is vital that Dozekar stays in that corner. All tanks should equally surround him to hold his position. If he moves too far, get all tanks on one side to push him back. Pushing him into the wall can warp him to his spawn point, which is deadly. If a tank begins to get to around 50% life from the AE, back out of the battle and go into the niche for a heal. Dozekar will aggro you if you get too low in health.<br>
<br>
It is important to keep him on the MT at all times. If the MT dies, get Dozekar on another by immediately backing all other tanks/casters off Dozekar except for that tank for 10-15 seconds. Casters nuke Dozekar in waves. A primary wizard calls for nukes at intervals of 20% life. They can also just yell NUKE AT WILL at around 75%, and casters sparsingly toss nukes on him throughout the remainder of the battle. At that time, nukers run in, drain mana on him, and back out. Clerics stay in the cubby at all times, as they can heal through the wall.<br>
<br>
It isn't as complicated as it sounds once you've tried it. He himself is also quite easy once you get the hang of the strategy.<br>
<br>
---<br>
<br>
As for safe spots besides the pit, I have personally been to two. The first one is the cubby where Travelakm and Lepthida spawn; no mobs wander there if people stay in the two niches. The other is smaller, but it is the named furthest back from the entrance, near the zone out. This one is not as safe, yet is only bothered by a lone wanderer or two. <p><b><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=54850>Gloobonious</a></b><br>60th Ogre Shaman<br>
